Description: include FL/platform.H in main-window.h for FLTK 1.4.5 Wayland builds
 main-window.h uses Pixmap (for _icon_pixmap/_icon_mask) and main-window.cpp
 uses fl_display, fl_xid, fl_open_display and XA_CARDINAL — all declared via
 FL/x11.H. In FLTK <= 1.4.4 and in X11-only FLTK 1.4.5 builds these symbols
 leaked through transitive FLTK headers. FLTK 1.4.5 with Wayland+X11 hybrid
 mode routes FL/platform.H through FL/wayland.H, which only includes FL/x11.H
 when FLTK_USE_X11 is defined. Adding an explicit FL/platform.H include
 restores the declaration chain on all platforms and all FLTK 1.4.5 backends.
Author: Foundry Linux <packages@foundrylinux.org>
Applied-Upstream: https://github.com/Rangi42/tilemap-studio/commit/ffcce44, master
Last-Update: 2026-06-13
--- a/src/main-window.h
+++ b/src/main-window.h
@@ -7,5 +7,6 @@
 #include <FL/Fl_Overlay_Window.H>
 #include <FL/Fl_Menu_Bar.H>
 #include <FL/Fl_Group.H>
 #include <FL/Fl_Native_File_Chooser.H>
+#include <FL/platform.H>
 #pragma warning(pop)
